                  <td class="tit_icon">MANAGEMENT OF THE AFFAIRS OF THE ASSOCIATION &amp; FUNDS</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="2%" valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td width="98%" align="left" class="text"><strong>ADMINISTRATION : </strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><ol>
                            <ul>
                              <li>The final  Authority of the Association shall vest in its General Body Meeting summoned in  such manner as is specified in the Articles of the Association. </li>
                              <li>&nbsp;The management of the affairs shall vest in  the Managing Committee duly constituted in accordance with Articles of the  Association.</li>
                              <li>Subject to the  direction given or resolution/regulation made by the meeting of the General  Body of the Association, the Committee shall exercise all powers, expressly  conferred on it and discharge all functions entrusted to it under relevant  Articles.</li>
                              <li>There shall be  various Committees formed as per exigencies for administering the Association.</li>
                            </ul></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15" valign="top"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left" ></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>FUNDS :</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><p>The  funds for the Association shall be collected in the following manner.</p>
                            <ul>
                              <li>Donations.</li>
                              <li>Admission and Membership fee.</li>
                              <li>Various Programmes arranged by the Association.</li>
                              <li>Income received from movable, immovable assets of the  Association. </li>
                              <li>Income received on investment.</li>
                              <li>Raising interest free loans.</li>
                            </ul></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                            <tr>
                              <td colspan="2" valign="top"><p><strong> (A) Provisions regarding Loans &amp; Deposits :</strong></p></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td width="2%" valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                              <td width="98%" align="left" class="text">The  Association can raise loans as decided by the Managing Committee for  fulfillments of the objects of the Association as specified by the Memorandum  of Association. The Association can invest its funds as decided by the Managing  Committee. The relevant provisions of the Bombay Public Trusts Act, 1950 shall  apply to the Association.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td height="15" valign="top"></td>
                              <td height="15" align="left" ></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td colspan="2" valign="top"><strong>(B) Provisions  Regarding Sale  and Purchase of Immovable  Property : </strong></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                              <td align="left" class="text">The Association can sell its property and also  purchase property in the name of the Association as decided by Managing  Committee. The relevant provisions of the Bombay  Public Trust Act, 1950 shall apply to the Association.</td>
